cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DS

The paper deals with Cross-language Information Retrieval (CLIR) which is a subfield of Information Retrieval (IR) and involves natural language processing (NLP) techniques. Therefore, cs.IR is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a probabilistic translation model which falls under the category of NLP and machine learning, making cs.CL and cs.LG likely sub-categories. The paper also uses a monolingual corpus and a bilingual dictionary, which involves data structures and algorithms, making cs.DS and cs.AI possible sub-categories.
